Three people died on Friday while another sustained serious injury after two lorries collided and burst into flames near Salama on the Mombasa-Nairobi Highway. Area police boss Charles Muthui said the driver of a canter which was headed to Nairobi, his loader and a passenger in the second lorry died following the incident. He said the accident occurred after one of the lorries tyre burst. "The driver of the trailer escaped but a passenger who was on board was burned beyond recognition," Muthui said. The bodies were taken to Machakos Level 5 Hospital mortuary. Click here for the latest political news  